@buddy2  

Seriously, have you not played standard in that era besides using caw blade? do you know how *ridiculous* it was? This card and [Jace, the Mind Sculptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jace, the Mind Sculptor) warped standard so *badly* WOTC had no choice but to ban them. Caw blade was too good and too powerful. It had answers to everything and could keep up with any deck. It wasnt uncommon to have 8 out of the 10 top places in any competition to be caw blade or a variant of it, the only other remote contenders were splinter-twin and MBC decks.  

Perhaps you are a *spike* who cares for nothing except winning. IMO you're the kind of people killing standard and making MTG a very unfun and "whoever has more money wins" game.
